cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on delivering high quality VR experience over wireless networks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with video quality in VR applications. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possible category as the paper proposes a scheduling policy for multiple VR users in a wireless system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper develops a predictive scheduling policy for the AP. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible category as the paper optimizes scheduling decisions in both proactive and deadline scheduling phases.
